e night with the hose in the driveway and I went viral Okay You know what Let's call it Henriette and Nan we don't need you to be on any Zoom calls Oh wonderful","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":326.62,"end":328.0,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_04","text":"Thank God","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":328.9,"end":329.44,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_08","text":"Okay","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":329.9,"end":332.8,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_01","text":"Hey does anybody know where I can find Nan's hose video","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":333.52,"end":337.82,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_00","text":"Yeah I'll send it to everybody Thanks brother Oh thank you Thanks guys","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true}],"summary":"Main topics\n- Introduction to using Zoom for Sales Corp Industries’ first team call and a quick tutorial.\n- Team dynamics and humor about working from home, plus attempts to use Zoom features (layouts, virtual backgrounds, screen share).\n- Privacy, security, and on-camera mishaps during a test run (camera angles, what’s visible on screen, personal content).\n- Operational decision about future Zoom participation for certain staff and a light-hearted afterword.\n\nKey points and conclusions\n- Attendees include Brian (Sales), Crystal (Market Research), Kevin (Research), and receptionists Henriette and Nan. The session doubles as both a tutorial and a social check-in on home setups.\n- The group experiments with Zoom features: changing layouts, applying virtual backgrounds, and sharing screens. Several distractions and mishaps arise, including unintended screen content and an awkward on-camera moment.\n- Privacy and security concerns surface: participants worry about what a hacker could see, and there are remarks about avoiding exposing personal content (e.g., camera mishaps, avatars).\n- A clear decision is made: Henriette and Nan should not participate in future Zoom calls, as “we don’t need you to be on any Zoom calls.”\n- A humorous, closing thread emerges: a request to locate Nan’s “hose video,” with a promise to share it with the group.\n\nAction items (implied)\n- Team members will continue to explore Zoom features (layouts, backgrounds) while minimizing on-screen exposure of personal content.\n- Someone plans to circulate Nan’s hose video to the group as a joke, continuing the lighthearted tone.\n\nAttribution\n- Narrative and setup: Brian, Crystal, Kevin (participants) and Henriette/Nan (receptionists) are referenced throughout, with chaotic on-call moments attributed to the group as a whole.","title":"Zoom Call Chaos at Sales Corp Industries","transcript":"Hey everybody, hi, welcome to Sales Corp Industries first Zoom call. This is how we're going to be doing meetings now. So we wanted to get everyone acquainted with the program with a little Zoom tutorial. On the call today we got Brian from sales. Oh man, it's so good to see everybody, at a safe distance that is. Yeah, we got Crystal from market research. Sorry my place is such a wreck. Nah, it looks perfect. We got Kevin from research. Are any of y'all wearing pants? Be honest now. Zoom is fun. Uh oh, it is, it is. And of course, Henriette and Nan, our fun receptionists. Yeah, it is. Well, we just work the phones normally, so we're going to see. Hello, hello, I got an email address for this. That's great. We're glad to have you. You guys will be just fine. Zoom has different layouts, so go ahead and play around with the view on your screen while we chat. Anybody up to anything fun at home? Well, mainly like a lot of my cat looking at me like, shouldn't you be at work? Yeah, I know, my dogs are so happy right now. I take them on like 12 walks a day. Does anyone else fully hate their kids? And for me, it's been re-evaluating which of my mugs I think are the funniest. Okay, now this isn't right, is it? Yes, and I recorded my own commentary for a dog's purpose. I think this is not right. You just don't need to be so close to the camera. Okay, well, I've been calling into QVC and telling them how good of a job I think that they're doing. Just reset the camera. Okay, like this? Did I activate Zoom? Nope, you turned it off, and it looks like your avatar is a picture of Wayne Brady. Henriette and Nam, guys, just point the camera at you and just leave it be. We're not cut out for this. I thought this computer only did Solitaire. We ruined the Zoom. No, no. Hey, don't cry. No one ruined the Zoom. We're all learning here, okay? Why don't I just show you guys some of the other cool features it has, okay? Like there's virtual background. Even though you're at home, you can change the background to a beach or wherever you'd most like to be. This is my beach. It's the only file I have on my computer, and it's my favorite doctor. The poster from The Good Doctor? He's a doctor, but he's different. Okay, yeah. You can also share your screen down here. Oh, wow. Either your desktop or an application. Okay, am I doing it? I was going for desktops. What part of my screen are you seeing? We're seeing a Google search that says, Siri, is my daughter pregnant? Okay, but I was wondering if a hacker gets a hold of a Zoom. What can they tell? What can they tell about me? No, no, no, no, no, no. Please don't bring it into the bathroom. We can see you always. I didn't know. Okay, my screen is dark again. Darn it. No, don't take your clothes off, Nan. No, no, no, no, no. Don't take your clothes off. Oh, my God. No, don't. Stop. Both of you. I'm sorry to do this, guys. Just please stop. Please. Oh, no. I'm bad news. I'm from hell. I just found out I'm supposed to tip waiters. I found out I've been wearing my shoes on the wrong feet. Ah. Okay, Henriette, Nan, don't be so hard on yourselves, guys. This technology is new. You're staying home. I'm sure you're great at that. No, we're not. I've never used soap before. I used my license as toilet paper, and now I don't know my own birthday. Okay, that's probably enough. My husband says I can only use one sheet of toilet paper, but I need three to get all the dookie out. If I can't kiss my kids on the mouth, I'm going to hurt an animal. I tried to clean my ass in the middle of the night with the hose in the driveway, and I went viral. Okay. You know what? Let's call it. Henriette and Nan, we don't need you to be on any Zoom calls. Oh, wonderful. Thank God. Okay. Hey, does anybody know where I can find Nan's hose video? Yeah, I'll send it to everybody. Thanks, brother. Oh, thank you. Thanks, guys.","transcriptChunks":[{"start":0.0,"end":7.920000076293945,"text":"Hey everybody, hi, welcome to Sales Corp Industries first Zoom call.","words":[{"start":0.0,"end":0.8199999928474426,"text":"Hey"},{"start":0.8199999928474426,"end":1.440000057220459,"text":"everybody"},{"start":1.6399999856948853,"end":3.2200000286102295,"text":"hi"},{"start":3.680000066757202,"end":4.699999809265137,"text":"welcome"},{"start":4.699999809265137,"end":5.139999866485596,"text":"to"},{"start":5.139999866485596,"end":5.559999942779541,"text":"Sales"},{"start":5.559999942779541,"end":6.019999980926514,"text":"Corp"},{"start":6.019999980926514,"end":6.599999904632568,"text":"Industries"},{"start":6.599999904632568,"end":7.239999771118164,"text":"first"},{"start":7.239999771118164,"end":7.559999942779541,"text":"Zoom"},{"start":7.559999942779541,"end":7.920000076293945,"text":"call"}]},{"start":8.619999885559082,"end":10.680000305175781,"text":"This is how we're going to be doing meetings now.","words":[{"start":8.619999885559082,"end":8.979999542236328,"text":"This